   up to six interviews as part of the AIDS Costs and Services Utilization
   Survey (ACSUS). ACSUS was an 18-month panel survey of patients in care
   for HIV/AIDS at 26 sites located in 10 U.S. cities. Poisson regression
   analyses with generalized estimating equations were conducted to
   determine the effects of demographic and socioeconomic variables on the
   acquisition rate of antiretrovirals, antipneumocystics, and
