   activities was an important predictor of subsequent high levels of
   depressive symptoms. However, some activity domains were more closely
   linked to the onset of new depressive symptoms than others. In
   particular, declines in the ability to perform recreational activities
   and engage in social interactions were linked to the onset of new
   depressive symptoms.
