   Study of Labor Market Experience in Youth (NLSY). The symptom items were
   related to the covariates using the statistical technique of structural
   equation modeling generalized to dichotomous outcomes. The present model
   is a special case of structural equation modeling, a multiple causes and
   multiple indicators (MIMIC) model, in which one or more latent variables
   (i.e., alcohol abuse and dependence) intervene between a set of observed
   background variables predicting a set of observed response variables
   (i.e., DSM-IV symptom items).
