   model for DSM-IV criteria found in other studies and provide further
   support for the validity of alcohol dependence in general population
   samples. A major implication of the factor structure in the present
   study relates to the different classification of cases that would
   otherwise be obtained with DSM-IV criteria. These departures were shown
   to affect abuse, which retained only 40% of DSM-IV diagnoses, more
   strongly than dependence, which retained 91% of DSM-IV diagnoses.
