   to measure children's dental health in this study, with the exceptions
   of caries experience in the permanent teeth and sealant presence, were
   inversely related to the communities' SES. The percentage of children
   with dental sealants was directly related to the community's SES.
   Practice Implications. Further improvements in oral health will
   necessitate that community-based preventive programs and access to
   quality dental care be made available to children who are identified as
   being at highest risk of experiencing oral disease.
