   applied, data analysis can exploit simplifying assumptions because good
   experimental design removes correlations among independent variables
   that exist nature, outside the experiment, as well as effects of
   unmeasured variables. Where the science is, of necessity, observational,
   these simplifications can not be guaranteed and, as a result, the
