   proportion of the homeless had made one or more hospital visits over the
   prior 3 months than the nonhomeless. After multivariate adjustment,
   doubled-up participants were found to make more emergency room visits,
   the homeless were less likely to be taking prophylaxis for Pneumocystis
   carinii pneumonia, and both the doubled-up and the homeless were shown
   to use slightly more outpatient care than the stably housed.
