   patterns across stably housed. doubled-up. and homeless HN-infected
   persons after controlling for health insurance coverage. These
   differences, especially those pertaining to outpatient services, suggest
   that the unstably housed may be receiving less adequate health care than
   the stably housed, and hence may he more likely to experience adverse
   clinical outcomes.
