   debate is often situated in the false problems of sociology, since it is
   seen as a particular form of the perennial and irresolvable dilemma
   between social nominalism and realism, as well as between freedom and
   determinism. Nevertheless,the debate is far from over within
   contemporary sociology and other social science, as indicated by the
