   Hall Indians being more similar to those of the local Whites than to
   other American Indians. All groups ranked storage of nuclear material,
   storage of additional nuclear material, and spills and accidents as the
   most serious of a list of concerns provided about the site. Fort Hall
   Indians answered an open-ended question with concerns for population
   levels and migration routes of game animals and other wildlife, more
   than hunting and human health. The Shoshone-Bannock from Fort Hall
