   risk of hospitalization for affective psychosis for those born in
   Copenhagen versus rural areas. Obstetric complications had a moderate
   sized relationship to schizophrenia, but the relationship of urban birth
   to schizophrenia was unaffected by adjustment for obstetric
   complications.
