   be a useful tool for quick and efficient estimation of mortality rates
   among under 5 year olds in countries where good mortality data are not
   routinely available. This is especially true for countries with complex
   humanitarian emergencies where information on mortality changes can
   guide interventions and the social stability to use standard demographic
